@startuml
title User Registration & Token Flow

actor User
participant "Client UI" as UI
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "TokenService" as Token
participant "API Gateway" as Gateway
participant "ResourceService" as Resource

== Registration / Login ==
User -> UI : Navigate to Registration/Login
UI -> Auth : POST /auth/register\n{ username, password }
Auth --> UI : 201 Created /error
note right of Auth : Stores user credentials\n(e.g. hashed password)

User -> UI : Submit Login Form
UI -> Auth : POST /auth/login\n{ username, password }
Auth -> Token : createToken(userId, scopes)
Token --> Auth : { accessToken, refreshToken }
Auth --> UI : 200 OK\n{ accessToken, refreshToken }

== Accessing Protected Resource ==
User -> UI : Click “Get Profile”
UI -> Gateway : GET /api/profile\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken>
Gateway -> Auth : validateToken(<accessToken>)
Auth --> Gateway : valid | invalid
alt valid
    Gateway -> Resource : GET /profile?userId=<from token>
    Resource --> Gateway : 200 OK\n{ profileData }
    Gateway --> UI : 200 OK\n{ profileData }
else invalid
    Gateway --> UI : 401 Unauthorized
end

== Token Refresh ==
note over UI, Auth: When accessToken expires
UI -> Auth : POST /auth/refresh\n{ refreshToken }
Auth -> Token : refreshToken(oldRefreshToken)
Token --> Auth : { newAccessToken, newRefreshToken }
Auth --> UI : 200 OK\n{ newAccessToken, newRefreshToken }

@enduml